1 members shall elect a chairman and other officers as the commission may deem appropriate.
2 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a majority of the commission shall constitute
3 a quorum for the transaction of business and all official actions of the commission shall
4 require the affirmative vote of a majority of the members present and voting.
5 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of the commission shall serve
6 without compensation, except per diem or expense reimbursement to which they may be
7 individually entitled as members of their constituent organizations.
8 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that Senate Legislative Services shall provide staff
9 support for the commission.
10 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the commission shall terminate on the date of
11 the submission of its report or August 1, 2027, whichever occurs first.
12 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
13 Governor Jeff Landry.
